ygData.subject: Re: Marriage
ygData.msgSnippet: The wedding was wonderful, for those who could not attend.  We were a bit delayed in starting because one of the guests kept getting attacked by the guards.
ygData.messageBody:
The wedding was wonderful, for those who could not attend. We were a bit delayed in
starting because one of the guests kept getting attacked by the guards. After he
dispatched 6 of them in haste, they left him alone and the wedding continued. Logos
gave a WONDERFUL service (highly recommend him). And many were there who remembered
our first meeting and who had stood by me through Corellon's long illness.

The wedding night was also disturbed, this time by a Dark Elf whom we dispatched with
extreme prejudice *grin*. We are now honeymooning in Unrest, and I got to see the
great Agathorn today, though the circumstances were less than ideal as he was called to
mediate a dispute, it was truely wonderful as I had never seen him before.

So, if you're in Unrest on Quellious, say hi.

Dnaice

> From: "Suzanne J. Johnson" <katannah@...>

> I'm a shmoe. My dad's birthday is today, and I totally forgot (I swear, I think I
> got thrown by that whole 7th/8th Saturday/Sunday thing too). Dnaice, I wanted so
> badly to be at your festivities, but there isn't a way possible. I hope you will
> forgive me and appreciate the sentiment that I wanted to be there. I hope your big
> day is as wondrous as a girl could wish for, and that you are surrounded by your
> friends and chosen family, and feel truly loved, respected, and cherished. I wish
> you the best of adventures and most glorious of hunts, and I hope Corellon
> appreciates the treasure he is being gifted with--your love and companionship.
